<item>
            <title>[SHIRO-462] Authentication exceptions are swallowed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SHIRO-462</link>
                <project id="12310950" key="SHIRO">Shiro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In org.apache.shiro.cas.CasFilter.onLoginFailure(AuthenticationToken, AuthenticationException, ServletRequest, ServletResponse) the passed-in AuthenticationException is not logged anywhere. In my case, a misconfigured SSL certificate error was being swallowed. The lack of logging meant I had to use a debugger to see the exception details.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is a similar issue with the other override of this method, in org.apache.shiro.web.filter.authc.FormAuthenticationFilter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggest logging at debug level (which is off by default in sensible setups, but can be enabled during investigations). See attached patch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
